{"lemma":"مَرَّةُ","slug":"مَرَّةُ","root":"م.ر.ر","root_slug":"م-ر-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/م-ر-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مَرَّة","root":"مرر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":20},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","adv","noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n38371","n3691","n38372","n38373"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a time, instance, occurrence","tags":["adverbial","usually"],"examples":[{"text":"ذَاتَ مَرَّةٍ","english":"once; one time"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ellipsis of اِسْمُ مَرَّةٍ (ismu marratin)","tags":["abbreviation","alt-of","ellipsis"]},{"pos":"adv","gloss":"once","examples":[{"text":"حَرَصَ جُحَا عَلَى تَجَنُّبِ غَضَبِ زَوْجَتِهِ وَمَرَّةً...","english":"Joha was keen to avoid his wife's anger and once ..."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bile","examples":[{"text":"كرمدانة.\nالماهية: حبها يمدحه الأطباء.\nأعضاء النفض: تسخن القبل جدًا وتسهل الماء والمرّة.","english":"Myrtle seed.\nWhat it is: Its seed is praised by the physicians.\nPalpitating organs: It heats the front well and releases the waters and bile."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"strength, energy, resilience, constancy","tags":["figuratively"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"feminine singular of مُرّ (murr)","tags":["feminine","form-of","singular"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/mar.ra/","/mar.ra.tan/","/mir.ra/","/mur.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n38371","headword_ar":"مَرَّةٌ","root":"mr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A time; one time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the sense of the French"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fois;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taArapN","text_ar":"تَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one action; a single action"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"act;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~N","text_ar":"مَرٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K: [but see what follows:]) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bout; an instance; a case;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single temporary offection"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attack; a fit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as, for instance, of hunger, thirst, disease, and the like:] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~aAtN","text_ar":"مَرَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miraArN","text_ar":"مِرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirarN","text_ar":"مِرَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~N","text_ar":"مَرٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather this is a coll. gen. n. of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~apN","text_ar":"مَرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the n. un.] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muruwrN","text_ar":"مُرُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) the last on the authority of Aboo-'Alee, and occurring in the following verse of Aboo-Dhu-eyb:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"tanak~arota baEodiY A^amo A^aSaAbaka HaAdivN\n                     \n                     \n                        mino Ald~ahori A^amo mar~ato Ealayoka muruwru"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hast thou become altered since I saw thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hath an accident of fortune befallen thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"have vicissitudes come upon thee?"},{"kind":"text","text":"] but Es-Sukkaree holds that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mrwr","text_ar":"مرور"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an inf. n.; and IJ says, I do not think this improbable, and that the verb is made fem. because the inf. n. implies muchness and genus. (M.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalotuhu mar~apF","text_ar":"فَعَلْتُهُ مَرَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I did it once"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (A, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~aAtK","text_ar":"مَرَّاتٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miraArFA","text_ar":"مِرَارًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"several times"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA@lomar~api","text_ar":"بِا@لْمَرَّةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"At once."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiyahu *aAta mar~apK","text_ar":"لَقِيَهُ ذَاتَ مَرَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He met him once"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: only used adverbially: (M, K:) so says Sb. (M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiyahu *aAta AlmiraAri","text_ar":"لَقِيَهُ ذَاتَ المِرَارِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He met him many times:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) [or this has a different signification; for] you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yaSonaEu *`lika AlA^amora *aAta AlmiraAri","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يَصْنَعُ ذٰلِكَ الاَمْرَ ذَاتَ المِرَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one does that thing sometimes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes he leaves it undone. (ISk, S.) Also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiy^otuhu mar~FA A^awo mar~ayoni","text_ar":"جِيْتُهُ مَرًّا اَوْ مَرَّيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~apF A^awo mar~atayoni","text_ar":"مَرَّةً اَوْ مَرَّتَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came to him once"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twice"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, K.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","A","S","M","K"]},{"entry_id":"n3691","headword_ar":"مَرَّةٌ","root":"tA^r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a time, whether long or short;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiynN","text_ar":"حِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAar:) sometimes, however, it is pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taA^orapN","text_ar":"تَاْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiy^arN","text_ar":"تِيَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiy^aArN","text_ar":"تِيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) these are pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taA^orapN","text_ar":"تَاْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taArapN","text_ar":"تَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAraAtN","text_ar":"تَارَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiyarN","text_ar":"تِيَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tyr","text_ar":"تير"},{"kind":"text","text":", and K and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"twr","text_ar":"تور"},{"kind":"text","text":",) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiyaArN","text_ar":"تِيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tyr","text_ar":"تير"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"twr","text_ar":"تور"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","IAar","T"]},{"entry_id":"n38372","headword_ar":"مُرَّةٌ","root":"mr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mur~N","text_ar":"مُرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n38373","headword_ar":"مِرَّةٌ","root":"mr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~a","text_ar":"مَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~a bihi","text_ar":"مَرَّ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amar~ahu EalaY Aljisori","text_ar":"اَمَرَّهُ عَلَى الجِسْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"act of passing, passing by"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beyond, going, going away, passing away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.] El-Aashà says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^alaA qulo litay~aA qabola mir~atihaA A@solamiY"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Now say to this damsel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this little female,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taA","text_ar":"تَا"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before her passing, Be thou safe"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A firm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong, twisting."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  Hence, (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Strength:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, A, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strength of make:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirarN","text_ar":"مِرَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amoraArN","text_ar":"اَمْرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) In the Kur, [liii. 6,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw mir~apK","text_ar":"ذُو مِرَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The angel"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Jibreel"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gabriel"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Fr, K, * TA:) whom God hath created endowed with great strength. (TA.) You say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN *uw mir~apK","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ ذُو مِرَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A strong man."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA taHil~u AlS~adaqapu liEiniY~K walaA li*iY mir~apK sawiY~K","text_ar":"لَا تَحِلُّ الصَّدَقَةُ لِعِنِىٍّ وَلَا لِذِى مِرَّةٍ سَوِىٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The giving of alms to one who possesses competence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"riches, is not allowable, nor to him who has strength and is sound in limbs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Intellect:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strength of intellect:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sound judgment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"firmness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iHokaAmN","text_ar":"اـِحْكَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mataAnapN","text_ar":"مَتَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TK.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu la*uw mir~apK","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَذُو مِرَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is possessed of intellect and sound judgment and firmness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  Also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A strand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"single twist, of a rope;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mariyrapN","text_ar":"مَرِيرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L, * TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirarN","text_ar":"مِرَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almir~apu","text_ar":"المِرَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The gall, bile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"choler;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the humours of the body;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which are four;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraArap","text_ar":"مَرَارَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or [rather]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almir~ataAni","text_ar":"المِرَّتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"denotes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two of the four humours of the body;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[namely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the yellow bile"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~aforaA='u","text_ar":"الصَّفْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the black bile"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~awodaA='u","text_ar":"السَّوْدَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":");]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the other two humours being the blood"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~amu","text_ar":"الدَّمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the phlegm"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albalogamu","text_ar":"البَلْغَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mzj","text_ar":"مزج"},{"kind":"text","text":":) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miraArN","text_ar":"مِرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","ISk","S","A","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}